So how does it work?
In a nutshell, players use their smartphones to search for Pokémon, which are tracked by GPS, and after being found, can be "photographed" (via a screenshot of the phone) or "captured".
The generation that played the game at a younger age has joined in the hype and jumped off the couch to join the search.
