Many public health campaigns’ calls to “find 30,” “get up from the couch,” and “be active every day” have yielded no results because most public health warnings are boring and cared about by people who look unhappy.
The importance of exercise cannot be underestimated.
People who move regularly have a lower risk of developing cancer or depression.
Activity helps with weight management, high blood pressure and diabetes. Its benefits are too varied to list here.
The great thing about Pokémon Go is that it makes people go out and do something they enjoy.
This covers the three pillars of health: exercise, fresh air and sunshine, and fun.
Some people even make new friends when they hunt.
